# Kapur Cold Storage ŌĆö ERP Style Guide

This app is an **operations ERP** (daybook, inventory, ledgers, reports). UI must stay **readable under long shifts**, **scannable in data-heavy screens**, and **polished on phones** used on the warehouse floor.

**Stack:** React, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui, CSS variables in `src/index.css`. Do not invent parallel color systemsŌĆöuse semantic tokens (`background`, `foreground`, `primary`, `muted-foreground`, `destructive`, etc.).

---

## 1. Typography

| Role | Font | Classes |
|------|------|---------|
| Body, forms, tables | Inter (`font-sans`) | `text-sm` default; `leading-normal` or `leading-relaxed` for paragraphs |
| Page & section titles | Outfit (`font-heading`) | `font-heading text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight` (page), `text-base font-semibold` (section) |
| Labels & captions | Inter | `text-sm font-medium` (label), `text-xs text-muted-foreground` (hint) |
| Micro copy only | Inter | `text-xs` ŌĆö never for primary data or amounts |

**Readability rules**

- Minimum **14px (`text-sm`)** for any data the user must read or compare; **16px (`text-base`)** for form inputs (prevents iOS zoom on focus).
- Never use `text-[10px]` or `text-[11px]` for numbers, IDs, or ledger lines.
- **Contrast:** body text = `text-foreground`; secondary = `text-muted-foreground` only for labels/hints, not amounts or statuses.
- **Truncation:** `truncate` + `min-w-0` on flex children; always pair with `title` attribute or tooltip for full value.
- Headings: `text-foreground` only ŌĆö avoid `text-muted-foreground` on titles.

```tsx
// Page header
<h1 className="font-heading truncate text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground sm:text-2xl">
  Daybook
</h1>

// Section inside a page
<h2 className="font-heading text-base font-semibold text-foreground">Today&apos;s entries</h2>
```

