## 2. Numbers, currency & quantities (ERP-critical)

All monetary values, weights, bag counts, and rates must be **easy to scan and align**.

| Rule | Implementation |
|------|----------------|
| Tabular alignment | `tabular-nums` on every numeric cell and stat |
| Font for figures | Prefer `font-sans tabular-nums`; use `font-mono tabular-nums` only for IDs, voucher numbers, or codes |
| Amounts | `text-sm font-medium text-foreground`; negatives: `text-destructive` + leading minus, never parentheses alone |
| Decimals | Consistent precision per domain (e.g. money: 2, weight: 3); format in code with `Intl`, not raw floats in UI |
| Alignment | Amounts & quantities: **`text-right`** in tables; labels stay left |
| Locale | Default **`en-IN`** for display (`Intl.NumberFormat`, `Intl.DateTimeFormat`) unless product specifies otherwise |
| Large numbers | Use grouping (e.g. `12,34,567.89`); for very large totals consider compact notation in cards only, full value in detail/tooltip |
| Units | Separate column or muted suffix: `500 <span class="text-muted-foreground">kg</span>` ŌĆö never bury unit inside the number string |

```tsx
<span className="tabular-nums text-sm font-medium text-foreground">
  {new Intl.NumberFormat('en-IN', { style: 'currency', currency: 'INR' }).format(amount)}
</span>
```

**Do not:** center-align money columns, use `text-xs` for totals, or rely on color alone for debit/credit (add `+` / `ŌłÆ` or DR/CR label).

