## 7. Mobile & responsive

Breakpoint: **`md` (768px)** ŌĆö matches `useIsMobile()` / sidebar behavior.

| Area | Mobile | Desktop |
|------|--------|---------|
| Sidebar | Sheet / icon rail via shadcn `Sidebar` | Expanded `collapsible="icon"` |
| Topbar | `SidebarTrigger` + truncated title; hide username (`hidden lg:inline`) | Full user chip |
| Tables | Horizontal scroll + sticky first col; card list alternative for &lt;5 columns | Full table |
| Dialogs | Prefer `Sheet` side `bottom` or full-screen for complex forms | `Dialog` centered |
| Spacing | `p-4`, `gap-3` | `p-6`, `gap-4`ŌĆō`gap-6` |
| Toasts | `position: "bottom-right"` (see login) ŌĆö avoid covering primary FAB |

**Mobile elegance**

- No horizontal page overflow ŌĆö `min-w-0` on flex children, `overflow-x-auto` only on table wrappers.
- Avoid nested scroll areas (sidebar + page + card) without clear affordance.
- Primary actions: bottom-aligned or full-width on narrow screens.
- Test **320px** width and **safe-area-inset** for notched devices when adding fixed footers.

---

## 8. Icons, buttons & actions

- Icons: `lucide-react`, default `size-4`; `size-3.5` only in compact table rows.
- One **primary** button per view; destructive actions require confirmation.
- Icon-only controls: `aria-label` required (see `ThemeToggle` in `app-topbar.tsx`).
- Button sizes: `default` / `sm` in toolbars; `h-11` for main mobile CTAs.

---

## 9. Feedback & states

- **Toast:** `sonner` for success/error after mutations.
- **Loading:** `Loader2 className="size-4 animate-spin"` inline; disable button while pending.
- **Skeleton:** match final layout dimensions ŌĆö prevents layout shift.
- **Errors:** human-readable message; retry when network-related.

---

## 10. Accessibility & field conditions

- Focus: visible ring (`focus-visible:ring-ring/30`) ŌĆö do not remove outlines.
- Target **WCAG AA** contrast for `foreground` on `background` and `primary-foreground` on `primary`.
- Support **dark mode** via `next-themes` ŌĆö every new surface must work in `.dark` tokens.
- Bright environments: avoid low-contrast gray-on-gray for critical numbers; use `text-foreground` for data.

---

